title: Xochitl Ortiz Ross
text:
Hi there! 👋
My name is Xochitl (pronounced só-chill). I am a Ph.D. candidate in the Ecology and Evolutionary Biology department at UCLA in the Blumstein Lab. I am a behavioral ecologist studying the long-term consequences of early-life adversity in wild yellow-bellied marmots (check-out my latest paper).
